OL,3,CHow man-made snow is ensuring a future
OL,4,Cfor Scotland's ski resorts
OL,6,FMost Scottish resorts say they used to
OL,7,Fenjoy snow from before Christmas,
OL,8,Fwhich would last through to beyond
OL,9,FEaster, but in the last few years,
OL,10,Fmany have reported that snow is not
OL,11,Farriving until mid-February and is
OL,12,Fgone by the end of March.
OL,14,FAccording to the Met Office, the
OL,15,Fnumber of snowfall days in Scotland
OL,16,Fhas dropped by between 25 and 30%
OL,17,Fsince the 1970s, and it has warned
OL,18,Fthat by 2080, there will be winters
OL,19,Fwhere Scotland sees no snow at all.
